properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 16 at 8:43PM PST until February 17 at 3:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt,
strongest nw of San Nicolas Island. Combined seas 6 to 11 feet
when conditions are worst.

* WHERE...Outer waters from Santa Cruz Island to San Clemente
Island to 60 NM offshore including San Nicolas and Santa
Barbara Islands.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 3 AM PST Monday. For the
Small Craft Advisory, from 3 AM Monday to 3 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will create dangerous sea conditions
which could capsize or damage small and large vessels.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...See the Coastal Waters Forecast (CWFLOX).
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
